The paper deals with decision making and learning, which are core topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Gaussian processes and pairwise comparisons for preference modelling suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the proposed strategies using computer and human-based experiments indicates a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. The use of clustering and ranking techniques suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the real-world study on traffic regulation suggests a focus on social and information sciences (cs.SI).
